title: revamp of submods and nested tokens
body:
This makes nested tokens be part of the submods part of the token with a more unified results.

It gets rid of the submod name claim and uses the map label instead.

It adds the attachment claim which describes how securely submod is attached.

title: Be cwt
body:
Big rearrangement:
- separate information and data model using CDDL
- say an EAT is a CWT or JWT

No new claims or any substantive change to any claim.

I believe I have largely succeeded in using CDDL for the information model and
defining later how it translates to the CWT and JWT data models.  It seems like
this is what CDDL is for, but others don't seem to be using it this way (yet). Being 
new to CDDL and attempting what others seem to have not, I may have made some errors since I have no example to follow.

title: First draft of CBOR interop section
body:
CBOR has a lot of different data type and for each type there are encoding variations. In order for EAT to have good interoperability, there has to be a specification for what types and variants to use. 

(Seems to me that other CBOR-based protocols like COSE and CWT should have similar).
